events.description: Liu Bang is enthroned as the Emperor of China, beginning four centuries of rule by the Han dynasty.
events.html: • 202 BC – Liu Bang is enthroned as the Emperor of China, beginning four centuries of rule by the Han dynasty.[1]

events.description: The Fourth Council of Constantinople closes.
events.html: • 870 – The Fourth Council of Constantinople closes.[2]

events.description: Aztec king Cuauhtémoc is executed on the order of conquistador Hernán Cortés.
events.html: • 1525 – Aztec king Cuauhtémoc is executed on the order of conquistador Hernán Cortés.[3]

events.description: The Scottish National Covenant is signed in Edinburgh.
events.html: • 1638 – The Scottish National Covenant is signed in Edinburgh.[4]

events.description: Elias Lönnrot signed and dated the first version of the Kalevala, the so-called foreword to the Old Kalevala.
events.html: • 1835 – Elias Lönnrot signed and dated the first version of the Kalevala, the so-called foreword to the Old Kalevala.[5]

events.description: A gun explodes on board the steam warship USS Princeton during a pleasure cruise down the Potomac River, killing six, including Secretary of State Abel Upshur. President John Tyler, who was also on board, was not injured from the blast.
events.html: • 1844 – A gun explodes on board the steam warship USS Princeton during a pleasure cruise down the Potomac River, killing six, including Secretary of State Abel Upshur. President John Tyler, who was also on board, was not injured from the blast.[6]

events.description: The United Kingdom ends its protectorate over Egypt through a Unilateral Declaration of Independence.
events.html: • 1922 – The United Kingdom ends its protectorate over Egypt through a Unilateral Declaration of Independence.[7]

events.description: The Charlevoix-Kamouraska earthquake strikes northeastern North America.
events.html: • 1925 – The Charlevoix-Kamouraska earthquake strikes northeastern North America.[8]

events.description: February 28 incident: In Taiwan, civil disorder is put down with the death of an estimated 28,000 civilians.
events.html: • 1947 – February 28 incident: In Taiwan, civil disorder is put down with the death of an estimated 28,000 civilians.[9]

events.description: The 1948 Accra riots erupted following a march by ex-servicemen of the Gold Coast Regiment towards the seat of the colonial government at Christiansborg Castle where they were fired upon by Superintendant Colin Imray leading to the killing of Sergeant Adjetey, Corporal Attipoe and Private Odartey Lamptey and the arrest of the Big Six in the Gold Coast.
events.html: • 1948 – The 1948 Accra riots erupted following a march by ex-servicemen of the Gold Coast Regiment towards the seat of the colonial government at Christiansborg Castle where they were fired upon by Superintendant Colin Imray leading to the killing of Sergeant Adjetey, Corporal Attipoe and Private Odartey Lamptey and the arrest of the Big Six in the Gold Coast.[10][11][12]

events.description: A school bus in Floyd County, Kentucky hits a wrecker truck and plunges down an embankment into the rain-swollen Levisa Fork river. The driver and 26 children die in one of the worst school bus accidents in U.S. history.
events.html: • 1958 – A school bus in Floyd County, Kentucky hits a wrecker truck and plunges down an embankment into the rain-swollen Levisa Fork river. The driver and 26 children die in one of the worst school bus accidents in U.S. history.[13]

events.description: Discoverer 1, an American spy satellite that is the first object intended to achieve a polar orbit, is launched but fails to achieve orbit.
events.html: • 1959 – Discoverer 1, an American spy satellite that is the first object intended to achieve a polar orbit, is launched but fails to achieve orbit.[14]

events.description: A NASA T-38 Talon crashes into the McDonnell Aircraft factory while attempting a poor-visibility landing at Lambert Field, St. Louis, killing astronauts Elliot See and Charles Bassett.
events.html: • 1966 – A NASA T-38 Talon crashes into the McDonnell Aircraft factory while attempting a poor-visibility landing at Lambert Field, St. Louis, killing astronauts Elliot See and Charles Bassett.

events.description: The 1969 Portugal earthquake hits Portugal, Spain and Morocco.
events.html: • 1969 – The 1969 Portugal earthquake hits Portugal, Spain and Morocco.[15]

events.description: The British election ended in a hung parliament after the Jeremy Thorpe-led Liberal Party achieved their biggest vote share since 1929.
events.html: • 1974 – The British election ended in a hung parliament after the Jeremy Thorpe-led Liberal Party achieved their biggest vote share since 1929.[16]

events.description: In London, an underground train fails to stop at Moorgate terminus station and crashes into the end of the tunnel, killing 43 people.
events.html: • 1975 – In London, an underground train fails to stop at Moorgate terminus station and crashes into the end of the tunnel, killing 43 people.[17]

events.description: The final episode of M*A*S*H airs, with almost 110 million viewers.
events.html: • 1983 – The final episode of M*A*S*H airs, with almost 110 million viewers.[18]

events.description: The Provisional Irish Republican Army carries out a mortar attack on the Royal Ulster Constabulary police station at Newry, killing nine officers.
events.html: • 1985 – The Provisional Irish Republican Army carries out a mortar attack on the Royal Ulster Constabulary police station at Newry, killing nine officers.[19]

events.description: Olof Palme, 26th Prime Minister of Sweden, is assassinated in Stockholm.
events.html: • 1986 – Olof Palme, 26th Prime Minister of Sweden, is assassinated in Stockholm.[20]

events.description: Space Shuttle Atlantis is launched on STS-36.
events.html: • 1990 – Space Shuttle Atlantis is launched on STS-36.[21]

events.description: Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms (ATF) agents raid the Branch Davidian church in Waco, Texas with a warrant to arrest the group's leader David Koresh, starting a 51-day standoff.
events.html: • 1993 – Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms (ATF) agents raid the Branch Davidian church in Waco, Texas with a warrant to arrest the group's leader David Koresh, starting a 51-day standoff.[22]

events.description: An earthquake in northern Iran is responsible for about 1,100 deaths.
events.html: • 1997 – An earthquake in northern Iran is responsible for about 1,100 deaths.[23]

events.description: A Turkish military memorandum resulted in the collapse of the coalition government in Turkey.

events.description: During the religious violence in Gujarat, 97 people are killed in the Naroda Patiya massacre and 69 in the Gulbarg Society massacre.
events.html: • 2002 – During the religious violence in Gujarat, 97 people are killed in the Naroda Patiya massacre and 69 in the Gulbarg Society massacre.

events.description: Pope Benedict XVI resigns as the pope of the Catholic Church, becoming the first pope to do so since Pope Gregory XII in 1415.
